-- Global Rubber Demand To Advance 15.3% This Year, Rubber Study Group Says
-- B y   S u p u n n a b u l   S u w a n n a k i j
-- 2010-12-17T03:36:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/global-rubber-demand-to-advance-15-3-this-year-rubber-study-group-says.html
Global demand for natural and
synthetic rubber is forecast to increase by 15.3 percent this
year to 24.3 million metric tons, according to International
Rubber Study Group. Consumption worldwide is expected to expand
by 6.3 percent next year, it said. Natural-rubber supply is
estimated at 10.2 million tons this year, the group said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Supunnabul Suwannakij in Bangkok at 
